value.title: Hunter Biden emails: Giuliani attorney questions if FBI dismissed potentially damaging findings

value.title: Trump determined to avoid Hillary Clinton's fatal campaign blunder

value.title: Barrett declines to answer if Trump can pardon himself

value.title: Durbin says Trump administration case against ObamaCare is 'orange cloud' over Barrett nomination
value.excerpt: Sen. Dick Durbin, D-Ill., continued Democrats' claims that the real reason why Republicans are rushing to confirm Judge Amy Coney Barrett to the Supreme Court is so that she can be on the bench for an upcoming ObamaCare case, but he had a particularly colorful way of putting it.

value.title: 'Suburban women, will you please like me?': Trump attempts to appeal to voter group he has struggled to reach
value.excerpt: "Suburban women, will you please like me? Please. Please. I saved your damn neighborhood, OK?" Trump said at a rally Tuesday.

value.title: Trump to coronavirus victims: 'I feel your pain because I've felt your pain'
value.excerpt: The president told a crowd in Johnstown, Pennsylvania, that he "felt like Superman" after getting an experimental drug treatment for Covid-19 and that he's now "immune."

value.title: US election 2020: Do celebrity endorsements help Joe Biden?
value.excerpt: With just three weeks until the US presidential election, Democratic candidate Joe Biden seems to have cornered at least one constituency: celebrities. In recent days, many of the country's most famous voters have lined up to support Mr Biden and his running mate Kamala Harris.

value.title: New Jersey mayor's Facebook post blasting Trump and his supporters prompts outcry

value.title: Kamala Harris' false 'Honest Abe' story and her misuse of American history

value.title: Russia dismisses Trump administration efforts to secure nuclear arms deal before election
value.excerpt: The Kremlin on Tuesday rejected assertions by the Trump administration that the US and Russia had come to a "gentlemen's agreement" on extending a key arms control agreement and dismissed the idea that a deal would be reached before the US presidential election.
